Note: Moved from my Thingiverse profile since the site is perma-broken it appears

Provides a version of Woddish's excellent Tiny Tank Classic Mbt (now gone), KMFP proto-rhino concept, and a Scorpios launcher of unknown source, and a radar from Chris John, that have been sliced into major parts that are enabled to be quickly swapped and edited for customization by changing visibility of components between different options for hatches, side doors, symbols/icons, and crew. The eventual end game would be the ability to build any Deimos based Monoceros chassis vehicle with this tool.

This is intended for designers and modelers to product their own faction customized vehicles from in a standardized and high quality form.

If you like what I did and want to leave a tip it would be appreciated.
https://paypal.me/jimmyzimms

Edit 20220526: Found some flipped normals I missed and a couple of positioning errors so corrected. Since 3D Builder gets annoyed about nonmanifold object and does the wrong thing occasionally I've updated all the parts, even if it shouldn't matter.

Edit 20230112: Added a slicer for the side doors to the blender file that can be used by designers to make form fitting symbols from that can be set into the hatches.

Edit 20230426: Added support for KMFP's nifty 3rd edition style Whirlwind Launcher

Edit 20230519: With permission, incorporated thewraeththu's better Scorpius into the builder.

Edit 20230908: Updated the Scorpius launcher to have an upper deck based on the Deimos predator. This better matches to the updated plastic kit from GW.

Edit 20240117: Minor cleanup

Edit 20240518: For those that like rivets and bolts, two sets (based on the geometry of each glacis option) have been added to adorn your tanks with tons of extra! Thanks TC63 for the contributions!

Edit 20241027: Added in crew from the Rapax From Deimos builder here.

Provides a version of Woddish's excellent Tiny Tank Fancy APC and related things that have been sliced into major parts that are enabled to be quickly swapped and edited for customization by changing visibility of components between different options for hatches, side doors, symbols/icons, and crew. The eventual end game would be the ability to build any Mars based Monoceros chassis vehicle with this tool.

This is intended for designers and modelers to product their own faction customized vehicles from in a standardized and high quality form.

If you like what I did and want to leave a tip it would be appreciated.
https://paypal.me/jimmyzimms

Leverages Orcstain's excellent astartes symbols and bolter from Lord Chronos. Crew figure based on a DangItBlobby jarhead

New part contributions are welcome!

20211201: Added Door symbols for 1st founding chapters. Big shout out to Orcstain for knocking out symbols!

20211205: Added support for crafting razorbacks

20211216: Added support for Whirlwinds (missile pods adapted from JahnZizka)

20220104: Added GK/Inq symbols (adapted from Manbeast and TZRock). Hyperios pods graciously donated by Wolfkeeper to make WW Hyperios tanks.

20220112: Added Extra Armour plates for those that want to model some heavy Rhinos like the FW upgrade kit from years past.

20220426: I've corrected some small mesh and alignment issues. I have additionally added a how to use guide for those new to Blender

20220501: Added support for Hunter AA using rejiggered parts from zstu1979

20220526: Clean up on some nasty meshes and crunched file size down

20220906: Added GK symbols for hatch and doors

20230524: Added Lamenters chapter symbols

20230903: Added chaos trim and iconography

20231023: Corrected mesh error on right rear tread. Added Rainbow Warriors hatch and door iconography.

20231220: Added Death Company iconography

20240117: Updates to correct some minor geometry issues uncovered

20240429: Added Retributors icons

20240515: Normalized all the iconography between all the builders to have the same sets.

Edit 20240617: Incorporated numerous sets of stowage options for turrets and chassis donated by the community to give additional variety to your tanks.

Edit 20241024: Added option for open copula hatch and crew from DaffMakes most excellent crew models into the builder. Now you can select if you want an open or closed hatch (former for the crew) and can chose from Multiple different poses in Mk4-Mk6 armour on your exported APC! Give you many new options for your customized armies.

If you like what I did and want to leave a tip it would be appreciated.
https://paypal.me/jimmyzimms

This is a Proxy for the MK1 Mars Pattern Rhino (AKA Rogue Trader Style).

Print at 100% for regular 6mm Epic scale
Print at 105% for "Truescale" 6mm
Print at 110% for 8mm New AT 2018 Scale

Suitable for FDM printing at <0.1mm Layer Heights and low speed (20mm-sec)

This is my first project in Fusion 360 and was started in SketchUp 2018. Enjoy!

CHANGELOG
2018-03-15 - Noticed that the Step Sill on the sides was warping during printing due to being pretty thin. Corrected.
2018-03-13 - A couple of updates this morning. I caught 3D Builder moving pieces around again. Pending any feedback, this model is COMPLETE! YAY!!!
2018-03-12 - NOTE: If you downloaded this thing prior to 9PM EST I have found a bug in the model caused by me running it through MS 3D Builder. This bug caused a few mis-alignments between the parts that make up the various meshes. Please accept my apologies and re-download this model for the corrected files.
